datasetName: R. L. McGregor Herbarium Vascular Plants Collection
occurrenceRemarks: Growing only above 6500' to 8000' in Miller Canyon. Very infrequent in crevices on a sloping rock face (only 5 plants observed along a 4 mi trail). Inflorescences 60-80 cm long and leaves only basal. This was the only host plant for Mexalictus arizonensis Eickwort (Hymenoptera: Halictidae), a very rare bee found presently only in the Huachuca Mtns and the Santa Catalina Mtns. [Voucher for entomological collection ARIZ1B00 017].
eventRemarks: Miller Canyon, 2.9 km W Hwy 92, 4.8 km from Miller Canyon Rd, along Miller Canyon Trail #106. Growing with Geranium and Erigeron in juniper and pine area.
